This project is an easy to use Bottle wrapper to Pystache.

To use Pystache with Bottle, import template handlers from pystache extension:

    from bottle.ext.pystache import view

    @route('/')
    @view('your_template')
    def func():
    	return {'hello': 'world'}

This wrapper define other handlers like core implemented templates do:

 * `PystacheTemplate`, `Template` 
 * `pystache_template`, `template`
 * `pystache_view`, `view`

Pystache is a Python implementation of Mustache.

Pystache: https://github.com/defunkt/pystache
Mustache: http://mustache.github.com

== Known bugs ==
* If you use partials, your partial templates should have the extension defined in `pystache.View.template_extension` (it is `mustache` by default), because because partial calls can't be handled by Bottle and Pystache works with only one file extension.
